00:00:22,757 --> 00:00:25,925
narrator: today on "how it's made"...       

5
00:00:53,354 --> 00:00:55,054
the invention of polyurethane 

6
00:00:55,056 --> 00:00:57,789
skateboard wheels in the early 1970s       

7
00:00:57,791 --> 00:01:00,893
suddenly made jumps and tight cornering possible  

8
00:01:00,895 --> 00:01:04,363
because these wheels had    
a better grip on riding surfaces

9
00:01:04,365 --> 00:01:07,066
than the old metal or ceramic wheels.       

10
00:01:07,068 --> 00:01:08,200
they were more durable,    

11
00:01:08,202 --> 00:01:11,136
and the shock absorption was greatly improved.     

12
00:01:13,908 --> 00:01:16,875
skateboard wheels come in different sizes,      

13
00:01:16,877 --> 00:01:19,578
hardness, colors and graphic designs.      

14
00:01:19,580 --> 00:01:21,647
for the rider, there are may practical    

15
00:01:21,649 --> 00:01:24,850
and aesthetic considerations. 

16
00:01:24,852 --> 00:01:29,154
making skateboard wheels starts
with a computer design.    

17
00:01:29,156 --> 00:01:32,858
a designer uses the software to guide cutting tools.    

18
00:01:32,860 --> 00:01:36,462
the tools carve into a solid aluminum puck   

19
00:01:36,464 --> 00:01:39,665
and transform it into one half of a wheel mold. 

20
00:01:43,370 --> 00:01:46,205
next, the other half of the mold takes shape    

21
00:01:46,207 --> 00:01:48,173
as the computerized tooling sculpts        

22
00:01:48,175 --> 00:01:50,109
another puck to a profile   

23
00:01:50,111 --> 00:01:52,511
that fits to the first one perfectly.         

24
00:01:56,117 --> 00:02:00,285
not all of the skateboard wheel
molds are two-part versions.  

25
00:02:00,287 --> 00:02:02,654
others are one-piece structures,

26
00:02:02,656 --> 00:02:07,192
each with a pin in the center to form a bearing cavity.   

27
00:02:07,194 --> 00:02:10,462
a nozzle dispenses freshly mixed polyurethane liquid   

28
00:02:10,464 --> 00:02:12,931
into the wheel molds.     

29
00:02:12,933 --> 00:02:15,834
the liquid starts to solidify immediately.    

30
00:02:17,938 --> 00:02:19,738
to complete the process,    

31
00:02:19,740 --> 00:02:22,407
a worker loads the polyurethane-filled molds 

32
00:02:22,409 --> 00:02:24,109
into an oven and bakes them         

33
00:02:24,111 --> 00:02:28,113
at almost 240 degrees fahrenheit
for 40 minutes.        

34
00:02:30,284 --> 00:02:33,719
during baking, any bubbles in the polyurethane rise    

35
00:02:33,721 --> 00:02:35,754
to the top and are diffused,       

36
00:02:35,756 --> 00:02:40,258
leaving solid forms with no weak spots.      

37
00:02:40,260 --> 00:02:43,395
workers remove the pins from the molds.        

38
00:02:43,397 --> 00:02:45,497
then it's on to the next station.      

39
00:02:49,436 --> 00:02:51,770
here, a worker blasts compressed air     

40
00:02:51,772 --> 00:02:54,206
between the wheels and the molds to pry      

41
00:02:54,208 --> 00:02:56,609
the wheels free and pop them out.       

42
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:02,281
another worker probes the wheel
using a durometer gauge    

43
00:03:02,283 --> 00:03:04,382
to ensure the urethane has cured

44
00:03:04,384 --> 00:03:07,119
to the right degree of hardness.

45
00:03:07,121 --> 00:03:09,621
if the sample wheel is sufficiently hard,     

46
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:12,557
the batch is ready for the next step.       

47
00:03:12,559 --> 00:03:15,794
the worker clamps       
the skateboard wheel in a lathe.

48
00:03:15,796 --> 00:03:17,329
the lathe spins the wheel   

49
00:03:17,331 --> 00:03:19,130
while an automatic cutter contours        

50
00:03:19,132 --> 00:03:22,334
the edges to a softer, more rounded profile.     

51
00:03:25,105 --> 00:03:28,373
to give the skateboard wheels some visual impact,   

52
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:30,375
an artists selects and arranges graphic      

53
00:03:30,377 --> 00:03:32,144
designs on a computer.     

54
00:03:34,314 --> 00:03:37,316
he prints a film negative of the images he's chosen.   

55
00:03:39,453 --> 00:03:42,520
a worker will use this negative
to produce a printing plate  

56
00:03:42,522 --> 00:03:44,590
from a piece of metal that's been coated       

57
00:03:44,592 --> 00:03:48,193
with a light-sensitive substance known as emulsion.  

58
00:03:48,195 --> 00:03:50,195
he places the film negative on the plate          

59
00:03:50,197 --> 00:03:52,631
inside a uv light chamber.   

60
00:03:52,633 --> 00:03:56,468
he closes the lid and activates the uv light.  

61
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:58,636
this triggers a photochemical reaction    

62
00:03:58,638 --> 00:04:01,707
that transfers the image from the negative to the plate.

63
00:04:04,545 --> 00:04:07,278
the worker then applies a solution that removes    

64
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,848
unexposed emulsion and, in the process,        

65
00:04:09,850 --> 00:04:14,453
etches the image into the printing plate.    

66
00:04:14,455 --> 00:04:16,588
he rinses off the chemicals.  

67
00:04:19,660 --> 00:04:23,228
next, he dries the plate to reveal the etched artwork. 

68
00:04:25,566 --> 00:04:27,899
another worker positions a magnetized          

69
00:04:27,901 --> 00:04:29,434
ink cup overview the image   

70
00:04:29,436 --> 00:04:32,004
and installs it in a pad printing machine.   

71
00:04:34,909 --> 00:04:37,810
an operator loads skateboard wheels onto posts       

72
00:04:37,812 --> 00:04:40,345
that index them forward for printing.         

73
00:04:44,518 --> 00:04:48,453
the ink cup deposits ink on the printing plate.   

74
00:04:48,455 --> 00:04:51,590
a silicone pad picks up the inked image and stamps   

75
00:04:51,592 --> 00:04:54,192
it onto the skateboard wheel. 

76
00:04:54,194 --> 00:04:57,062
the operator removes the printed wheel       

77
00:04:57,064 --> 00:05:00,498
and sets it on a tray.     

78
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:01,800
a technician now clamps    

79
00:05:01,802 --> 00:05:03,801
one of the wheels in a testing device,      

80
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:06,238
which will gauge the rebound. 

81
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:09,274
he drops a metal ball onto the wheel and measures  

82
00:05:09,276 --> 00:05:13,011
how high it bounces or rebounds.          

83
00:05:13,013 --> 00:05:16,815
a high rebound is desirable.  

84
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:21,486
these skateboard wheels are now cleared for shipping. 

85
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:25,157
a worker wraps the wheels in plastic and heat shrinks it.

86
00:05:27,628 --> 00:05:31,630
it takes about 3 days     
to make these skateboard wheels.

87
00:05:31,632 --> 00:05:35,133
but how long they'll last depends a lot on the rider

88
00:05:35,135 --> 00:05:37,536
and how he or she rolls.    

89
00:05:37,538 --> 00:05:38,904
♪♪         

